,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:35.744902360Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":341,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","author":"ubuntu","text":"Watch-semantics follow-up: benchmark and regression coverage should measure idle-heartbeat overhead, filter selectivity costs, cadence adaptation under churn and degraded sources, and the operational cost difference between durable event publication and ephemeral keepalive traffic.","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:06Z"},{"id":345,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","author":"ubuntu","text":"Historical-performance follow-up: benchmarks must measure replay and as-of latency, cache-hit versus reconstruction cost, payload-size behavior for historical responses, and SQLite churn introduced by replay caching so the feature stays operationally cheap enough for live debugging.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:28:15Z"},{"id":361,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: benchmark coverage must measure redaction and safe-preview cost on hot surfaces and replay paths so the safety layer remains cheap enough for routine robot consumption.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:28Z"},{"id":370,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","author":"codex","text":"Plan-space refinement: benchmark coverage now explicitly waits for 8.2 so user-facing cost checks include dashboard and alternate-renderer projection work, not only CLI renderers. Measure payload, allocation, and redaction or safe-preview overhead where those projections surface compact evidence.","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:45:40Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add redaction, sensitivity, and disclosure-control verification coverage","description":"Add dedicated verification for sensitivity, redaction, and disclosure-control semantics so ntm can prove richer robot data stay safe across persistence, replay, diagnostics, and transport boundaries.","design":"The tests should cover contract examples for visible versus preview_only versus redacted versus withheld payloads; rule-version and reason markers; safe-preview generation for pane output, mail snippets, diagnostic evidence, and replay snapshots; no-leak guarantees in SQLite projections, attention journals, incident replay caches, REST payloads, and streaming events; allowlisted-field behavior; and explicit diagnostic explanations for why content was transformed. Coverage should include package-local unit tests, SQLite and restart integration tests, Go-based e2e scenarios, and benchmark or regression checks for redaction cost and payload-size effects. Logging should be excellent: scenario name, schema ID, rule version, disclosure state, hidden-field counts, hashed evidence handles, replay mode, and diffs that prove raw secrets were not emitted.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the redesign has explicit automated coverage proving that sensitive material is transformed or withheld consistently across live surfaces, replay, persistence, diagnostics, and parity transports, and when failures produce enough detailed logging that a maintainer can understand exactly what leaked, what was expected, and which rule or surface misbehaved.","notes":"Sensitivity handling is too important to leave as an implied side effect of generic tests. If a regression could leak a secret without a dedicated failing test and clear artifact trail, this task is incomplete.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T01:34:08.838581790Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T21:14:46.082586209Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["robot-redesign","sensitivity","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.14","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:40.673125135Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:41.531532027Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:42.403226219Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:43.306247021Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:44.270220056Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:07:55.154188545Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:45:16.279676807Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:45.281933126Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:34:08.838581790Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:10:55.404469027Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:14:46.081642572Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:14:30.494368646Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:11:25.526905644Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:46.225757018Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:14:36.881297023Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:14:39.931320808Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:14:42.934427571Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":371,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","author":"codex","text":"Plan-space refinement: disclosure-control verification now explicitly waits for 8.2 so dashboard and alternate renderer paths cannot become an untested leak surface. Keep the logging artifact-rich enough to prove whether compact summaries, previews, and hidden evidence stayed within disclosure rules.","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:45:43Z"},{"id":378,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","author":"codex","text":"Plan-space refinement: 9.11 is now a true capstone for disclosure-control, so it waits on REST parity plus the base schema, unit, integration, e2e, and benchmark lanes it claims to span. That prevents a false \"safe\" state where redaction coverage is declared complete before the final REST path or before the underlying test suites exist to carry artifact-rich no-leak cases.","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:11:55Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.12","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add audit-trail and actor-attribution verification coverage","description":"Add dedicated verification for auditability and actor attribution so the redesign can prove operator-state changes, actuation loops, incident transitions, and disclosure decisions remain traceable across restart, replay, and transport boundaries.","design":"The tests should cover contract examples for actor-attributed attention-state changes, actuation request and outcome trails, incident lifecycle history, audit visibility in diagnostics or inspect flows, and the interaction between sensitivity redaction and audit usefulness. Coverage should include package-local unit tests for store APIs and event shaping, SQLite or restart integration tests for retention and replay behavior, Go-based e2e scenarios where multiple actors or sessions mutate state, and benchmark or regression checks that audit capture does not make hot paths noisy or expensive. Logging should be excellent: actor identifiers, origin classes, request IDs, affected references, timestamps, decision reasons, disclosure states, replay mode, and diffs that explain missing or malformed audit history.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when automated coverage proves that audit-worthy events are persisted and exposed consistently enough that a maintainer can answer who changed this, what request caused this effect, and why this disclosure or override happened, with detailed logs when any part of that trail breaks.","notes":"Auditability is a product feature here, not compliance theater. If a failure can erase or obscure operator trust history without a focused failing test, this task is incomplete.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T01:56:56.309450111Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T16:43:09.985831755Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T16:43:09.985369821Z","close_reason":"Verified implemented. audit_validation_test.go (494 lines): TestAuditEventStructure, ActorIDFormats, AttentionAcknowledge, AttentionSnooze, ActuationSend, ActuationInterrupt, IncidentCreate/Escalate/Resolve, DisclosureRedact, QueryByActor, QueryByTargetRef, RetentionPolicy, RedactionDoesNotObscureActor. audit_attribution_test.go (778 lines): ActorAttributionOnAttentionStateChange, ActuationRequestOutcomeTrail, IncidentLifecycleHistory, VisibleInDiagnostics, SensitivityRedactionPreservesUsefulness, MultiActorSessionMutation, PersistenceAcrossRestart. Full acceptance criteria coverage.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","robot-redesign","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.12","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:56:56.309450111Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add SQLite, adapter, degraded-source, and restart-recovery integration tests","description":"Add integration coverage for the runtime projection store, adapter normalization, degraded-source handling, attention replay, watermark persistence, incident evolution, and restart recovery behavior. This task exists because the hardest parts of the redesign live at the seams between subsystems, not inside isolated helper functions.","design":"The tests should exercise realistic sequences such as source outage followed by partial recovery, ntm restart followed by resumed delta computation, incident promotion after repeated evidence, projection rebuild with durable cursor continuity, ambiguous timeout followed by safe retry, duplicate request suppression with later verified outcome, repeated flapping source with cooldown and resurfacing, acknowledgment followed by material change and resurfacing, snooze expiry, pin and manual escalation behavior, retention or pruning decisions, and partial transport resync. They should use the shared deterministic harness and log scenario IDs, request IDs, idempotency keys, cursor transitions, watermark state, source_health changes, operator-state transitions, suppression or resurfacing markers, incident fingerprints, and assertion diffs with enough detail to diagnose failures quickly. This task should prove the redesign works as an operational system, not just as a collection of structs.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the critical persistence, degradation, replay, restart-safety, retry-safety, attention-hygiene, and operator-control promises of the redesign are pinned by deterministic integration tests that emit rich debugging context and fail loudly when those promises regress.","notes":"Future self: if you ever want to simplify something 'just for now,' make sure these tests still express the product promises that matter.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:27.316098652Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T22:01:09.699058328Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["integration","robot-redesign","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:26:19.161234835Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:52.934763148Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:17.490511841Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:16.320725277Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:16.842076218Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:36.296941786Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:17.376897885Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:26:20.009095793Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:04.649122301Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:09.455231992Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:17.928949556Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:26:07.866730187Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:27.316098652Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:18.057202776Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":348,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","author":"ubuntu","text":"Historical-replay test follow-up: integration coverage must exercise replay-window retention, restart-safe replay availability, partial-history and missing-source markers, cache invalidation, and degraded-source behavior so historical answers remain trustworthy after recompute and restart boundaries.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:28:29Z"},{"id":356,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: integration coverage must verify that restart, recompute, and degraded-source paths never reintroduce hidden raw content into projections, replay caches, or transport payloads.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:24Z"}]}
+{"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add SQLite, adapter, degraded-source, and restart-recovery integration tests","description":"Add integration coverage for the runtime projection store, adapter normalization, degraded-source handling, attention replay, watermark persistence, incident evolution, and restart recovery behavior. This task exists because the hardest parts of the redesign live at the seams between subsystems, not inside isolated helper functions.","design":"The tests should exercise realistic sequences such as source outage followed by partial recovery, ntm restart followed by resumed delta computation, incident promotion after repeated evidence, projection rebuild with durable cursor continuity, ambiguous timeout followed by safe retry, duplicate request suppression with later verified outcome, repeated flapping source with cooldown and resurfacing, acknowledgment followed by material change and resurfacing, snooze expiry, pin and manual escalation behavior, retention or pruning decisions, and partial transport resync. They should use the shared deterministic harness and log scenario IDs, request IDs, idempotency keys, cursor transitions, watermark state, source_health changes, operator-state transitions, suppression or resurfacing markers, incident fingerprints, and assertion diffs with enough detail to diagnose failures quickly. This task should prove the redesign works as an operational system, not just as a collection of structs.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the critical persistence, degradation, replay, restart-safety, retry-safety, attention-hygiene, and operator-control promises of the redesign are pinned by deterministic integration tests that emit rich debugging context and fail loudly when those promises regress.","notes":"Future self: if you ever want to simplify something 'just for now,' make sure these tests still express the product promises that matter.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_ty