ted_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:22.210017690Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:29.470416826Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:57:37.332066964Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:58:37.607802571Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:23.141843815Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:58:07.476650532Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":342,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Watch-semantics follow-up: repository docs and redesign notes must explicitly explain event taxonomy, heartbeat semantics, filtered subscriptions, replay-to-live transitions, and how operators or agents tell healthy quiet from broken quiet.","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:07Z"},{"id":349,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Historical-docs follow-up: the refreshed docs must clearly distinguish live snapshot, raw event replay, incident replay, and bounded as-of inspection, including when each is appropriate, what limits apply, and how degraded or partial history is explained to operators and agents.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:28:29Z"},{"id":358,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: docs must clearly explain what ntm redacts, when it emits safe previews, how disclosure markers should be interpreted, and why hidden evidence is still actionable rather than silently missing.","created_at":"2026-0