 {"id":"bd-pqwk","title":"Support partial/prefix session names for disambiguation","description":"Support partial/prefix session names for disambiguation.\n\n## Problem Being Solved\n\nCurrently you need to type full session name like `vnt destructive_command_guard`. Should support prefix matching.\n\n## Behavior\n\n- If prefix matches exactly one session: use it\n- If prefix matches multiple sessions: show matching options, ask user to be more specific\n- If prefix matches zero sessions: show error with available sessions\n\n## Examples\n\n```bash\n# Currently required\nntm view destructive_command_guard\n\n# Desired\nntm view destr  # works if only one session starts with 'destr'\nvnt destr       # same with alias\n\n# Ambiguous\nntm view my\n# Error: 'my' matches multiple sessions: my_project, my_test\n# Please be more specific.\n```\n\n## Implementation\n\nUpdate session name resolution in all commands:\n- ntm view SESSION\n- ntm kill SESSION\n- ntm send SESSION\n- ntm health SESSION\n- etc.\n\n## Robot Mode API\nRobot mode requires exact names (no fuzzy matching).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. Prefix matching works for all commands taking SESSION arg\n2. Exact match preferred over prefix match\n3. Multiple matches show list and error\n4. Zero matches show available sessions\n5. Robot mode requires exact names\n6. Works with vnt alias\n\n## Unit Tests (80% coverage target)\n- internal/session/resolve_test.go\n- Test exact match priority\n- Test unique prefix resolution\n- Test ambiguous prefix error\n\n## E2E Test Script\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# [E2E-PREFIX] Session Prefix Resolution Tests\nLOG_PREFIX=\"[E2E-PREFIX]\"\necho \"$LOG_PREFIX Testing prefix session names\"\nntm spawn test_session_one --cc=1 --no-prompt\nntm spawn test_session_two --cc=1 --no-prompt\nntm view test_session_o && echo \"Prefix worked\"\nntm kill test_session_one --force\nntm kill test_session_two --force\necho \"$LOG_PREFIX Prefix test complete\"\n```","acceptance_criteria":"1. Partial session names work for disambiguation\n2. Prefix matching finds unique session\n3. Multiple matches returns error with suggestions\n4. Works with all session-accepting commands\n5. Unit tests for matching logic\n6. E2E test with multiple sessions","notes":"## Testing Requirements\n- Unit tests: core logic, error paths, edge cases.\n- E2E scripts: full CLI/robot flow with detailed log/slog prefixes (e.g., [E2E-<AREA>]) and include session/agent/bead IDs.\n- If structured outputs are affected, assert schema stability + deterministic ordering.\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-19T06:46:15.575351270Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-01T23:00:17.536990467Z","closed_at":"2026-02-01T23:00:17.536922981Z","close_reason":"Prefix session-name resolution (exact>prefix), wired across core CLI commands; robot/json requires exact; unit tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-ptu2","title":"Task: Add event markers and details overlay","description":"## Overview\nAdd discrete event markers on the timeline with hover/select details.\n\n## Deliverables\n1. Event marker types:\n   - Prompt sent (▶): When user sends prompt to agent\n   - Completion (✓): When agent finishes a task\n   - Error (✗): When error detected\n   - Start/Stop (◆): Session lifecycle events\n\n2. Marker rendering:\n   - Small icons above timeline bar at event time\n   - Different colors for different event types\n   - Clustered markers when events too close together\n\n3. Details overlay:\n   - Show popup when marker selected\n   - Include: timestamp, event type, details\n   - For prompts: first 50 chars of message\n   - For errors: error message\n\n4. Interaction:\n   - Arrow keys to navigate between markers\n   - Enter to expand marker details\n   - Esc to close overlay\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- Use unicode symbols for markers\n- Popup positioning to avoid edge overflow\n- Cache marker positions for efficient navigation\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- Markers appear at correct times\n- Different event types visually distinct\n- Details overlay shows on selection\n- Navigation between markers works\n- Unit tests for marker placement","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-19T18:28:03.496917374Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-22T04:20:48.617338102Z","closed_at":"2026-01-22T04:20:48.617205812Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-ptu2","depends_on_id":"bd-3h0n","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-19T18:28:50.481921380Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-ptu2","depends_on_id":"bd-f815","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-19T18:28:03.512975659Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
