 {"id":"bd-vcmnv","title":"EPIC: CLI Help Simplification (minimal/full + optional suggestions)","description":"## Goal\nReduce cognitive overload without gating functionality.\n\n## Decision\n- Replace tiered/proficiency gating with a **simple help verbosity switch**.\n- Keep **contextual suggestions** as an optional, non-intrusive aid.\n\n## Scope\n- `ntm help --minimal` and `ntm help --full` (or equivalent)\n- Optional suggestions module (disable-able via config)\n- No changes to command availability\n\n## Non-Goals\n- No tiers, promotions, or usage tracking.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Minimal help is concise and stable\n- Full help remains complete\n- Suggestions are helpful but unobtrusive","notes":"## Testing Requirements\n- Unit tests: core logic, error paths, edge cases.\n- E2E scripts: full CLI/robot flow with detailed log/slog prefixes (e.g., [E2E-<AREA>]) and include session/agent/bead IDs.\n- If structured outputs are affected, assert schema stability + deterministic ordering.\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-01-19T18:58:24.926758550Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-11T17:53:09.504933844Z","closed_at":"2026-02-11T17:53:09.504914808Z","close_reason":"Epic complete: all sub-tasks implemented and verified in codebase","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-vcmnv","depends_on_id":"bd-22nh8","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-19T18:58:24.956061201Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-ve9hj","title":"Global spawn scheduler with paced pane/agent creation","description":"Implement a global spawn scheduler that serializes and paces all pane + agent creation (tmux new-session/split + agent process launch). Provide queueing, max concurrent spawns, and a rate limiter (token/leaky bucket with optional burst), preserving request ordering and fairness across sessions without removing any existing behaviors. Surface spawn progress/ETA in TUI/robot outputs so users can see queued work. Integrate hooks for guardrails/backoff. Tests: comprehensive unit tests for limiter math, queue fairness/ordering, starvation prevention, burst handling, and scheduler pause/resume; e2e script that spawns N panes and validates pacing via timestamps, absence of EAGAIN, and detailed spawn logs.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-24T03:19:38.539134018Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-24T09:44:00.476913992Z","closed_at":"2026-01-24T09:44:00.476356702Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["resource-limits","stability"]}
